{
  "texts": [
    "LORDD outperformed one in-dialect baseline and three cross-dialect baselines, while also bridging the gap with the skyline to 12% (down from 27.3%) and 25% (down from 64.7%) on similarity and accuracy respectively for en-IN.",
    "For en-NG, the gap is reduced to 5.8% (down from 17.9%) on similarity and 4.5% (down from 43.1%) on accuracy.",
    "Through ablation tests on LORDD, we validated the effectiveness of its components.",
    "Although TWP works with a restricted dataset and utilises turn-based dialogue, LORDD sets up the promise for dialect adaptation of decoder models.",
    "Our error analysis also highlights the scope for future improvement."
  ]
}